HEADWORD: Antiphone
<hw>An"ti*phone</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>The response which one side of the choir makes to the other in a
chant; alternate chanting or signing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

